      "title": "ℹ️ About — BrainDead Pixal3D",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "# 🧠 BrainDead — Pixal3D Image to 3D\n\nSingle image → textured 3D mesh. Pixal3D estimates geometry and texture from a single photo or generated image, outputting a TRIMESH compatible with all BD mesh nodes.\n\n## Flow\n1. **LoadImage** — load any image (single object works best; remove background first for clean results).\n2. **BD Pixal3D Preprocess** — background compositing + camera FOV estimation. Use `black` background mode for best geometry.\n3. **BD Pixal3D Image to 3D** — generates shape + texture. `1024_cascade` pipeline = best quality (~60 s). `1536_cascade` = higher resolution.\n4. **BD Preview 3D** — interactive 3D viewer in the canvas.\n5. **BD Export Mesh With Colors** — saves `.glb` (default) to ComfyUI output folder.\n\n## Models (auto-download on first run)\nPixal3D model (~10 GB) downloads from `TencentARC/Pixal3D` on first use. Model cached to `$HF_HOME`. Requires ~12 GB VRAM.\n\n## Tips\n- Use `fov_mode: auto_moge` unless you know the camera FOV of the source image (requires MoGe-2).\n- Use `fov_mode: manual` with `manual_fov: 0.2` if MoGe gives distorted results.\n- Pipe the mesh output into **BD OVoxel Bake** for full PBR texture extraction.\n- Works great after Flux/SD generation — generate → Pixal3D → game-ready asset in one workflow.\n\n---\n**BrainDeadGuild** — created by **BizaNator**\n[BrainDeadGuild.com](https://BrainDeadGuild.com) · [BrainDead.TV](https://BrainDead.TV) · [GitHub](https://github.com/BizaNator/ComfyUI-BrainDead) · [Discord](https://braindeadguild.com/discord)\n"
      ]
    },
